  <section style="pageLayout">
    <title style="chapterTitle">Chain Rule</title>

    <p style="sectionHeading">Introduction</p>

    <stack style="contentBG">
      <p>
        In this module we will cover the Chain rule for derivatives.
        The Chain rule is one of the core principals in calculus, and you're going to use it any time you take the derivative of a function even reasonably complex.
        The Chain rule can be a little daunting at first because we use it when we have a smaller function inside of a bigger function, in example: $ h(g(x)) $,
        and our goal is to take the derivative of $ h(g(x)) $.
      </p>
    </stack>


  </section>
















  <!--    SECTION 2    -->
  <sectionNoTitle style="pageLayout">
    <p style="sectionHeading">Chain Rule</p>

    <stack style="contentBG">
      <p style="centerText">
        Let $ f(x) = h(g(x)) $
      </p>
      <p style="centerText">
        The Chain rule tells us that the derivative of $ f(x) $, is equal to:
      </p>
      <p style="centerText">
        <style>
          <marginBottom>40</marginBottom>
        </style>
        $ f'(x) = h'(g(x)) \cdot g'(x) $
      </p>


      <style name="myWrap">
        <widthPercentage>0.93</widthPercentage>
        <horizontalAlignment>center</horizontalAlignment>
      </style>

      <style name="titleP">
        <marginTop>50</marginTop>
        <marginBottom>30</marginBottom>
        <size scale="large" />
        <foreground color="91 90 90" />
      </style>
    </stack>


    <p style="sectionHeading">Examples</p>



    <stack style="contentBG">

      <stack>
        <style>
          <horizontalAlignment>center</horizontalAlignment>
          <marginBottom>60</marginBottom>
        </style>

        <p style="subSectionHeading">Example 1</p>

        <table widths="10% 90%" grid="false">
          <row>
            <column>
              <image src="resources\question.png" inspect="false" />
            </column>
            <column>
              <p>Let $ F(x) = (3x + 1)^{3} $, find $F'(x)$ :</p>
            </column>
          </row>
        </table>



        <p>Let $ h(x) $ be the outside function and $ g(x) $ be the inside function. In this case we get: </p>

        <stack orientation="horizontal">
          <style>
            <widthPercentage>0.4</widthPercentage>
          </style>
          <p>$ h(x) = (-)^{3} $</p>
          <p>$ g(x) = 3x + 1 $</p>
        </stack>


        <p>
          <style>
            <marginTop>35</marginTop>
          </style>
          By applying the <b> Power rule </b>, we get:
        </p>
        <stack orientation="horizontal">
          <style>
            <widthPercentage>0.4</widthPercentage>
          </style>
          <p>$ h'(x) = 3(-)^{2} $</p>
          <p>$ g'(x) = 3 $</p>
          <style>
            <marginBottom>35</marginBottom>
          </style>
        </stack>



        <p>
          Finally, by applying the <b>Chain rule</b>, we get:
        </p>

        <p>$ F'(x) = 3(3x + 1)^{2} \cdot (3)  $</p>
        <p>$ F'(x) = 9(3x + 1)^{2} $</p>

      </stack>
    </stack>

    <p>
      <br />
    </p>

    <stack style="contentBG">
      <p style="subSectionHeading">Example 2</p>
      <table widths="10% 90%" grid="false">
        <row>
          <column>
            <image src="resources\question.png" inspect="false" />
          </column>
          <column>
            <p>$ F(x) = (x^{2} + 3)^{7}, $ find $ F'(x): $</p>
          </column>
        </row>
      </table>

      <stack name="answerWrap" style="collapsed">
        <p style="subSectionHeading">Answer</p>
        <table name="table" widths="10% 90%" grid="false">
          <row>
            <column>
              <image src="resources\answer.png" inspect="false" />
            </column>
            <column>
              <p>$ f(x) = (-)^{7} $ and $ g(x) = (x^{2} + 3) $</p>
              <p>$ f'(x) =  7(-)^{7 -1} $ and $ g'(x) = 2x $</p>
              <p>$ F'(x) = 7(x^{2} + 3)^{6} \cdot 2x $</p>
              <p>$ F'(x) = 14x(x^{2} + 3)^{6} $</p>
            </column>
          </row>
        </table>
      </stack>

      <button name="button1" content="Show Answer">
        <onClick>
          if button1.Text == "Show Answer" then
          answerWrap.Style.Visibility = "visible";
          button1.Text = "Hide Answer"
          else
          answerWrap.Style.Visibility = "collapsed";
          button1.Text = "Show Answer"
          end
        </onClick>
      </button>

    </stack>

    <p>
      <br />
    </p>

    <stack style="contentBG">
      <p style="subSectionHeading">Example 2</p>
      <table widths="10% 90%" grid="false">
        <row>
          <column>
            <image src="resources\question.png" inspect="false" />
          </column>
          <column>
            <p>$ F(x) = sin(2x), $ find $ F'(x): $</p>
          </column>
        </row>
      </table>

      <stack name="answerWrap" style="collapsed">
        <p style="subSectionHeading">Answer</p>
        <table name="table" widths="10% 90%" grid="false">
          <row>
            <column>
              <image src="resources\answer.png" inspect="false" />
            </column>
            <column>
              <p>$ f(x) = sin(x) $ and $ g(x) = 2x $</p>
              <p>$ f'(x) =  cos(x) $ and $ g'(x) = 2 $</p>
              <p>$ F'(x) = cos(2x) \cdot 2 $</p>
              <p>$ F'(x) = 2cos(2x) $</p>
            </column>
          </row>
        </table>
      </stack>

      <button name="button1" content="Show Answer">
        <onClick>
          if button1.Text == "Show Answer" then
          answerWrap.Style.Visibility = "visible";
          button1.Text = "Hide Answer"
          else
          answerWrap.Style.Visibility = "collapsed";
          button1.Text = "Show Answer"
          end
        </onClick>
      </button>

    </stack>
